* Iron Raptor let go of Prowl neck the very moment she felt him shudder, but 
hoping that he would be alright now that her saliva had repaired him. It 
always worked, she had to give credit to that.

She watched him roll over and sit up, but seeing him clench his jaw in pain.
Iron Raptor simply shifted her position and looked towards him, seeing if 
there was any other damage. There was none other then a few scratches and 
his broken wing.*

" You hit a few branches, disconnected your processor and broke your wing."

* But there was a tone of anger in her voice as well as concern. If he 
hadn't tried to grab her this would have never happened.
She growled.*

" And if you ever pull a stunt like that again it won't be branches that do 
that to you next time!"

* Iron Raptor then got to all four of her feet and glared towards Prowl, her 
eyes narrowed.*

" Now get back to base."
